developer_understanding_on_working: The configuration 'compressionQuality' is used in the code to determine the quality of compression when saving images to files. It is used in the compressJpeg method to specify the compression quality for JPEG images.
developer_understanding_on_triggering_fr: The 'compressionQuality' configuration is triggered whenever an image is being saved to a file in the system. The frequency of triggering depends on how often images are processed and saved.
developer_understanding_on_size_impact: The impact of the 'compressionQuality' configuration option is significant as it directly affects the file size of the saved images. Higher compression quality results in better image quality but larger file sizes, while lower compression quality reduces file size but may compromise image quality.
